        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer508280514" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11367178428200897344">Here&apos;s a book I&apos;ve heard about all my life, maybe more so the musical, and an author who couldn&apos;tbe more popular. He was a favorite of my grandfather&apos;s. I get the sense that his narrative voice may have been similar to the voice in my grandfather&apos;s head- the same matter-of-fact, US white male dominated world-view that pre-dated the 70&apos;s. Yet, still sensitive to all people and empathetic to the human condition. It was interesting to read this just after Guard of Honor- same war, same time period-</span>
  <span id="freeText11367178428200897344" style="display:none">Here's a book I've heard about all my life, maybe more so the musical, and an author who couldn'tbe more popular. He was a favorite of my grandfather's. I get the sense that his narrative voice may have been similar to the voice in my grandfather's head- the same matter-of-fact, US white male dominated world-view that pre-dated the 70's. Yet, still sensitive to all people and empathetic to the human condition. It was interesting to read this just after Guard of Honor- same war, same time period- 2 very different waiting games but with similar relationship tensions among genders, classes, ranks and ethnic groups. I applaud Michener for the sensory experiences he can manufacture and for playing around with narrative structures- chronology and narrators were unpredictable. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11367178428200897344" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

